g/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2468042097724228e-13, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3337}, {\"ngram\": \"performances\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3370}, {\"ngram\": \"Californian natives Billie Eilish\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3485}, {\"ngram\": \"2028 hosts\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britainended the Paris Olympics with 65 medals- the same amount won at London 2012 and second-best ever tally on foreign soil - with only the United States (126) and China (91) claiming more.\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3591, \"end\": 3602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999104148, \"rank\": 8.975336383158824e-11, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3662, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.921062829510867, \"rank\": 0.08562575605037512, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3686, \"end\": 3691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9486807630411493, \"rank\": 0.054069251676131753, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Great Britainended\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3532}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3551}, {\"ngram\": \"65 medals-\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3567}, {\"ngram\": \"the same amount\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3583}, {\"ngram\": \"ever tally\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3629}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign soil\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Team GB won eight fewer gold medals than in Tokyo three years ago and were 13 down on the 27 collected at Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3717, \"end\": 3724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999563443, \"rank\": 4.27752756061975e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9093166163555946, \"rank\": 0.0997269616748061, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"eight fewer gold medals\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3752}, {\"ngram\": \"Rio 2016\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A final return of 14 gold, 22 silver and 29 bronzesaw Britain slip to seventh spot in the medal table - its lowest place since finishing 10th at Athens 2004 - and third-best European nation behind hosts France and the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 4064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999937307803586, \"rank\": 6.269231246735243e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4037, \"end\": 4043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9963045212008897, \